{"id":1073,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":1073,"title":"Sarah or Sarai","subtitle":"","short_title":"Sarah or Sarai","uri":"/scriptures/bd/sarah","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/sarah.t1","order":".000.3552"},[".title","Sarah or Sarai"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/sarah.p1","order":".000.3553"},"Sarah means “princess.” The wife of Abraham. From",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/11.29?span=11.29-17.15"},"Gen. 11:29–17:15"],"the form of the name used is",["i","Sarai"],"(which possibly means “contentions,” or more probably is another form of",["i","Sarah"],"). She was married to Abraham before he left Ur. In her old age she became the mother of Isaac (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/21.2"},"Gen. 21:2"],"). She died before her husband and was buried in the cave of Machpelah at Hebron (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/23.2"},"Gen. 23:2"],"). See also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/isa/51.2"},"Isa. 51:2"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/4.19"},"Rom. 4:19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/11.11"},"Heb. 11:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-pet/3.6"},"1 Pet. 3:6"],"."]]],"refs":null}
